-- ── Freshdesk ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Freshdesk is an omnichannel customer support and helpdesk platform from Freshworks that unifies email, chat, phone, and social ticketing with automation and AI-assisted agent tools.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (limited-time program for up to 2 agents); paid plans start at $19/agent/month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2010, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$7000+ employees (Freshworks, parent company)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Mateo, California, United States (with a major engineering hub in Chennai, India)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$, $q$and 30+ additional languages$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Freshdesk Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Freshdesk review covering omnichannel ticketing, automation, AI features, pricing tiers, pros and cons, and top helpdesk alternatives for support teams.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Freshdesk is the original product of what is now Freshworks Inc., launched on October 13, 2010, from a rented meeting room in Chennai, India, by Girish Mathrubootham and Shan Krishnasamy. Mathrubootham had previously been VP of Product Management at ManageEngine, a division of Zoho Corp, and both founders identified a gap in the market for a more modern, easier-to-use customer support helpdesk than the enterprise incumbents of the time (notably Zendesk). Freshdesk signed its first customer, Atwell College in Australia, in June 2011 and reached 100 customers within 103 days of launch. In December 2011, venture firm Accel became the company's first institutional investor with a roughly $1 million investment. Freshdesk grew quickly on a freemium go-to-market model that undercut the pricing of established helpdesk software, and in 2016 the company launched its second major product, Freshsales, followed by other products under a broader platform strategy. In 2017, Freshdesk Inc. renamed itself Freshworks Inc. to reflect its expansion beyond the original helpdesk product, and in 2018 the company established a dual-headquarters model, with San Mateo, California becoming its global headquarters alongside its long-standing Chennai engineering base. Freshworks went public on Nasdaq on September 22, 2021, under the ticker FRSH, becoming the first Indian SaaS company to list on a U.S. exchange, with an IPO valuation reported around $10.1 billion.

As a product, Freshdesk today is an omnichannel customer support helpdesk. Its ticketing system consolidates conversations from email, live chat, phone, WhatsApp, and social channels into a single shared inbox, with collision detection to prevent multiple agents from replying to the same ticket. Automation is a core differentiator: Freshdesk offers rule-based ticket routing and prioritization, canned responses, and SLA management to keep response times on track, layered with 'Freddy AI,' Freshworks' AI brand spanning an AI-powered self-service agent, an AI copilot that assists human agents with drafting replies and summarizing tickets, and AI-driven insights for support leaders. The platform also includes a self-service knowledge base and customer portal, forums, field service management capabilities for scheduling and dispatching on-site technicians, and reporting/analytics dashboards for tracking team performance, CSAT, and ticket volume trends. A more advanced version, Freshdesk Omni, bundles ticketing with omnichannel and AI capabilities at a higher price point for teams that want the full communication stack without separately licensing add-ons.

Freshdesk's pricing has changed materially over the past two years. Historically, it offered a permanent 'Sprout' free-forever plan with up to ten agents; Freshworks reduced that free-tier agent allowance to two agents in November 2024 and, by mid-2025, discontinued the permanent free plan altogether, replacing it with a free program limited to one to two agents for a six-month window before requiring an upgrade. As researched, the current paid tiers are Growth at $19 per agent per month (annual billing), aimed at small teams wanting straightforward ticketing and a knowledge base; Pro at $55 per agent per month, the most commonly recommended tier for growing support teams needing multiple ticket views, custom roles, and advanced automation; and Enterprise at $89 per agent per month, aimed at large organizations needing advanced security, sandboxing, and audit capabilities. Freddy AI Copilot is priced separately as a $29-per-agent-per-month add-on across plans, and the Freshdesk Omni bundle (combining ticketing with broader omnichannel capability) is priced at roughly $29, $79, and $119 per agent per month across its own three tiers. Monthly billing (versus annual) typically costs about 20% more across all plans.

Freshdesk's target audience spans small businesses through large enterprises, though it has historically been strongest with small-to-midsize support teams attracted by its lower price point relative to Zendesk, its most direct competitor. Other competitors include Zoho Desk (particularly for businesses already using Zoho's suite), Help Scout (which targets smaller, more email-centric teams), Intercom (which leans more heavily into product-led, chat-first support with strong AI bot capabilities), and HubSpot Service Hub (which appeals to teams already using HubSpot's marketing and sales tools). Freshdesk differentiates primarily on affordability, ease of setup, and a broad included feature set even at lower tiers, while Zendesk and Intercom are frequently positioned as more enterprise-grade or more AI-forward, respectively. As part of the broader Freshworks portfolio alongside Freshsales (CRM), Freshservice (ITSM), and Freshchat/Freshmarketer, Freshdesk benefits from shared underlying AI infrastructure (Freddy AI) and cross-sell opportunities within Freshworks' publicly traded, multi-product business, which reported hundreds of millions in annual recurring revenue in recent fiscal years.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '3462f64d-8a5d-4bf1-aaf2-9bbe35c19498';

