-- ── Freshsales ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Freshsales is Freshworks' sales-first CRM that combines contact and deal management, built-in phone and email, and AI-powered lead scoring to help sales teams manage pipelines end to end.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (up to 3 users); paid plans start at $9/user/month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2016, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$7000+ employees (Freshworks, parent company)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Mateo, California, United States (with a major engineering hub in Chennai, India)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$, $q$and other Freshworks-supported languages$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Freshsales Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Freshsales CRM review covering pipeline management, AI lead scoring, pricing tiers, pros and cons, and top alternatives like HubSpot and Salesforce.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Freshsales is the customer relationship management (CRM) product built by Freshworks Inc., launched in 2016 as the company's second major product line after the success of its original helpdesk product, Freshdesk. Freshworks itself traces back to Girish Mathrubootham and Shan Krishnasamy's 2010 founding of Freshdesk in Chennai, India; by 2016 the company had grown enough to diversify beyond customer support into sales software, and it launched Freshsales to compete for the same small-and-midsize-business audience it had already built trust with through Freshdesk. In 2017, the parent company renamed itself from Freshdesk Inc. to Freshworks Inc. to reflect this broader multi-product strategy, which eventually also included Freshservice for IT service management and Freshmarketer for marketing automation. Freshworks completed its Nasdaq IPO in September 2021 under the ticker FRSH, and today operates a dual-headquarters model with its global headquarters in San Mateo, California, and a major engineering base in Chennai, India. Freshsales has at various points in its history also been marketed under the name 'Freshworks CRM' before reverting to the Freshsales name, reflecting Freshworks' periodic experiments with unified branding across its product line.

As a product, Freshsales is positioned as a 'sales-first' CRM, meaning its core workflows are built around helping sales representatives manage contacts and deals efficiently rather than around broader marketing automation (which Freshworks addresses separately through Freshmarketer). Its foundational features include contact and deal management with visual, customizable pipelines; a built-in phone dialer and email integration so reps can call and email prospects without leaving the CRM; and a unified customer timeline showing all touchpoints across channels. As deals move up Freshsales' pricing tiers, the platform adds more sophisticated capabilities: Freddy AI-powered lead scoring that ranks prospects by likelihood to convert, sales sequences for automated multi-step outreach campaigns, multiple sales pipelines for teams selling different products or serving different regions, territory management to assign accounts by geography or vertical, and workflow automation to reduce manual data entry and follow-up tasks. At the top of the range, Freshsales supports custom modules (letting businesses model unique objects beyond standard contacts and deals), field-level permissions for granular data access control, sandbox environments for testing configuration changes safely, audit logs for compliance and security tracking, AI-powered forecasting insights, and a dedicated account manager. Freshsales also integrates with other Freshworks products, allowing shared customer context between sales (Freshsales), support (Freshdesk), and marketing (Freshmarketer) teams operating on the same underlying platform, which Freshworks positions as a key differentiator versus assembling a stack of unrelated point solutions.

Freshsales' pricing follows a per-user, per-month model across four tiers plus a free option. As researched, the Free plan supports up to 3 users with basic contact and deal management, a built-in phone, and email integration, but excludes workflow automation, sales sequences, advanced reporting, and AI features. The Growth plan is priced at $9 per user per month on annual billing (around $11 monthly), and adds web forms, basic workflow automation, SMS and WhatsApp channel support, and a product catalog. The Pro plan is $39 per user per month annually (around $47 monthly) and is the first tier to unlock AI-powered lead scoring, sales sequences, multiple sales pipelines, and territory management, making it the plan most commonly recommended for teams that have outgrown basic contact management. The Enterprise plan is $59 per user per month annually (around $71 monthly) and adds custom modules, field-level permissions, sandbox access, audit logs, and AI-powered forecasting insights, aimed at larger, more complex sales organizations with compliance or customization needs. All paid plans include a 21-day free trial.

Freshsales' target audience is primarily small-to-midsize businesses (SMBs) and mid-market sales teams that want a CRM with less setup complexity and lower cost than enterprise-grade platforms, while still offering meaningful automation and AI capabilities as they scale. Its most frequently cited competitors are HubSpot CRM, which leads with strong inbound marketing automation and a generous free tier but can become expensive as businesses add HubSpot's other 'Hubs'; Salesforce Sales Cloud, which offers unmatched customization and ecosystem depth but at materially higher cost and complexity, generally favored by larger enterprises with intricate sales processes; Zoho CRM, a lower-cost competitor with a similarly broad software suite around it; and Pipedrive, a pipeline-first CRM that, like Freshsales, emphasizes simplicity for smaller sales teams. Freshsales differentiates primarily through its integrated AI (Freddy AI) across scoring, forecasting, and workflow suggestions, its tight integration with the rest of the Freshworks product suite for companies already using Freshdesk or Freshservice, and pricing that is generally positioned as more affordable than Salesforce and comparable to or cheaper than HubSpot at equivalent feature depth, particularly for SMB and mid-market sales teams evaluating total cost of ownership across a full sales tech stack.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '3791efda-beab-41cb-b03c-14070ac10a70';

